1
00:00:35,019 --> 00:00:40,021
(This drama is fictional and people or stories are not tied to reality.)

2
00:00:53,432 --> 00:00:57,038
Due to the Demon's temptation,

3
00:00:57,212 --> 00:00:59,508
so many people had to shed their blood.

4
00:01:05,182 --> 00:01:07,478
I gained more power as the king,

5
00:01:07,682 --> 00:01:11,217
but karma was always there to haunt me.

6
00:01:15,792 --> 00:01:18,988
I will take on all the karma.

7
00:01:19,562 --> 00:01:22,857
I want you to seal the Demon

8
00:01:24,202 --> 00:01:26,228
and do your best to avoid...

9
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:28,038
the consequences.

10
00:01:29,273 --> 00:01:31,267
I will do as you say, Father.

11
00:01:33,913 --> 00:01:36,107
Have you found traces of the Demon?

12
00:01:36,283 --> 00:01:38,247
It has disappeared.

13
00:01:38,952 --> 00:01:40,148
The Demon...

14
00:01:40,922 --> 00:01:42,618
never dies.

15
00:01:43,182 --> 00:01:45,187
Sealing it is the only way...

16
00:01:48,322 --> 00:01:49,517
Father!

17
00:01:50,163 --> 00:01:52,657
Father!

18
00:01:59,072 --> 00:02:01,137
Restore the king's portrait as soon as possible...

19
00:02:01,242 --> 00:02:03,908
so that we can seal the Demon once again.

20
00:02:04,913 --> 00:02:06,107
Yes, Your Majesty.

21
00:02:07,183 --> 00:02:08,611
But before we do that,

22
00:02:08,612 --> 00:02:11,647
we must find an artist who can restore the portrait.

23
00:02:12,082 --> 00:02:13,951
An artist who can portray divinity...

24
00:02:13,952 --> 00:02:16,321
so that the spirit of the Demon can be sealed.

25
00:02:16,322 --> 00:02:19,448
I am talking about artists like Gan Yong Guk and Hong Eun O.

26
00:02:27,302 --> 00:02:28,427
Find me an artist...

27
00:02:30,063 --> 00:02:31,267
no matter what.

28
00:02:31,873 --> 00:02:33,098
Yes, Your Majesty.

29
00:02:40,542 --> 00:02:44,752
(Episode 2: The Divine Artist)

30
00:02:44,753 --> 00:02:46,607
(Baekyu Painters Society)

31
00:02:47,082 --> 00:02:52,147
(19 years later, 31st year of King Seongjo)

32
00:04:27,353 --> 00:04:29,152
- Look. - Goodness.

33
00:04:29,153 --> 00:04:30,318
Let us go see.

34
00:04:31,453 --> 00:04:32,688
How beautiful.

35
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:36,217
Gosh, my heart is fluttering.

36
00:04:42,463 --> 00:04:45,301
My heart beats so fast just by watching.

37
00:04:45,302 --> 00:04:48,897
If your heart beats that fast just by looking at a painting,

38
00:04:49,643 --> 00:04:51,267
you should go see a doctor.

39
00:04:52,013 --> 00:04:54,637
- Hello. - I am sorry.

40
00:04:54,942 --> 00:04:56,137
Hurry.

41
00:05:02,223 --> 00:05:05,191
Among many different types of Sehwa paintings,

42
00:05:05,192 --> 00:05:07,488
let us learn about "The Old Man of the South Pole."

43
00:05:10,062 --> 00:05:12,988
What is most important when it comes to Sehwa paintings?

44
00:05:14,562 --> 00:05:17,498
Obviously to finish it by the due date.

45
00:05:18,302 --> 00:05:20,837
Otherwise, no one will buy it.

46
00:05:21,473 --> 00:05:23,041
- She is right. - That is correct.

47
00:05:23,042 --> 00:05:24,508
She has a point.

48
00:05:25,713 --> 00:05:27,068
Finishing it quickly...

49
00:05:28,713 --> 00:05:31,777
is not the most important thing when it comes to Sehwa paintings.

50
00:05:33,482 --> 00:05:36,318
How short this man is. The deer he is riding.

51
00:05:36,752 --> 00:05:38,318
The protruding head.

52
00:05:38,393 --> 00:05:42,017
You must portray these exact characteristics.

53
00:05:42,692 --> 00:05:45,988
That is how you form a lucky omen.

54
00:05:46,132 --> 00:05:48,762
You made an excellent choice by hiring him...

55
00:05:48,763 --> 00:05:50,428
as today's lecturer.

56
00:05:50,603 --> 00:05:52,972
Choi Jung, a painter from Gohwawon,

57
00:05:52,973 --> 00:05:55,198
came here to teach them himself.

58
00:05:55,302 --> 00:05:58,267
No lecture would be better for the painters.

59
00:05:58,413 --> 00:05:59,767
My goodness.

60
00:06:00,413 --> 00:06:02,111
You fool.

61
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:04,748
You need to do more than just copy the paintings.

62
00:06:04,882 --> 00:06:07,352
When it comes to Sehwa paintings, it is most important...

63
00:06:07,353 --> 00:06:10,988
to use clear colors and portray joy in the paintings.

64
00:06:11,492 --> 00:06:14,121
In other words, you must portray people's longing desire...

65
00:06:14,122 --> 00:06:16,421
to be blessed with luck, joy,

66
00:06:16,422 --> 00:06:19,858
happiness, and beauty.

67
00:06:21,002 --> 00:06:22,798
She really is something.

68
00:06:23,002 --> 00:06:25,798
Painter Hong, if you are done,

69
00:06:25,903 --> 00:06:28,402
stop causing trouble and just leave.

70
00:06:28,403 --> 00:06:30,198
I was going to leave.

71
00:06:36,843 --> 00:06:37,948
- Master Choi. - Gosh, you startled me.

72
00:06:38,482 --> 00:06:40,678
Uncle Chun Bok, here you go.

73
00:06:40,982 --> 00:06:43,548
I need to go somewhere. I will be right back.

74
00:06:43,583 --> 00:06:47,017
Where are you going at this hour, young lady?

75
00:06:47,792 --> 00:06:52,027
Where is she going every night?

76
00:06:52,792 --> 00:06:56,498
Probably to the market to meet Hong Eun O.

77
00:06:58,703 --> 00:07:01,668
Chun Bok, do you know something?

78
00:07:02,273 --> 00:07:05,142
Do you know how long she has been taking care of her father?

79
00:07:05,143 --> 00:07:06,472
Yes, 20 years.

80
00:07:06,473 --> 00:07:08,881
You already told me dozens of times.

81
00:07:08,882 --> 00:07:10,282
So you do not need to remind me...

82
00:07:10,283 --> 00:07:13,381
She was just a little girl...

83
00:07:13,382 --> 00:07:15,782
who couldn't see a thing.

84
00:07:15,783 --> 00:07:19,092
One rainy day, her vision returned...

85
00:07:19,093 --> 00:07:21,358
and told me she needs to make money to take care of her father.

86
00:07:21,862 --> 00:07:25,162
She asked me to teach her how to paint...

87
00:07:25,163 --> 00:07:28,832
and said she will chop firewood and do the dishes.

88
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:31,871
The skies must have been touched by her filial devotion...

89
00:07:31,872 --> 00:07:33,472
and gave her sight back.

90
00:07:33,473 --> 00:07:36,202
And just like her father,

91
00:07:36,203 --> 00:07:38,842
she not only quickly learned how to paint,

92
00:07:38,843 --> 00:07:42,207
but she was also very talented.

93
00:07:42,283 --> 00:07:45,077
I could not help but care for...

94
00:07:46,482 --> 00:07:47,618
her.

95
00:08:58,223 --> 00:09:00,188
Look at how handsome he is.

96
00:09:00,223 --> 00:09:02,757
There is more to him than that. He is also a gentleman.

97
00:09:02,823 --> 00:09:05,757
I heard he is favored by His Majesty.

98
00:09:06,032 --> 00:09:08,227
Look at him glow.

99
00:09:13,402 --> 00:09:16,072
What is going on? What is all the fuss about?

100
00:09:16,073 --> 00:09:17,342
You know why.

101
00:09:17,343 --> 00:09:19,408
Scholar Ha is on duty tonight.

102
00:09:19,872 --> 00:09:22,481
But then again, even I think...

103
00:09:22,482 --> 00:09:25,007
he is as handsome as I am.

104
00:09:26,213 --> 00:09:29,948
At the end of the day, he is blind. They are unbelievable.

105
00:09:30,083 --> 00:09:31,991
- By the way, - Yes?

106
00:09:31,992 --> 00:09:33,792
I heard Scholar Ha was the helper...

107
00:09:33,793 --> 00:09:35,261
of the rainmaking ritual that took place 19 years ago.

108
00:09:35,262 --> 00:09:36,262
Yes.

109
00:09:36,263 --> 00:09:39,292
Did he really lose his sight that day?

110
00:09:39,293 --> 00:09:41,001
Yes, that is correct.

111
00:09:41,002 --> 00:09:44,028
That was when it finally rained in nine years.

112
00:09:44,132 --> 00:09:47,172
Is that why he is called the guarding spirit of this place?

113
00:09:47,173 --> 00:09:49,342
What are you talking about?

114
00:09:49,343 --> 00:09:52,107
He is nothing but a freak.

115
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:00,048
Scholar Ha is here.

116
00:10:02,382 --> 00:10:03,818
Hello, Scholar Ha.

117
00:10:03,953 --> 00:10:05,422
- Hello. - Hello.

118
00:10:05,423 --> 00:10:07,092
Let us begin the observation.

119
00:10:07,093 --> 00:10:08,717
We will begin with the Vermilion Bird of the South.

120
00:10:08,992 --> 00:10:11,327
We will begin with the Vermilion Bird of the South.

121
00:10:11,362 --> 00:10:12,491
- Yes. - Yes.

122
00:10:12,492 --> 00:10:14,028
Let us begin the observation.

123
00:10:17,132 --> 00:10:20,727
The fifth star is extremely bright today.

124
00:10:21,142 --> 00:10:24,038
Someone special will come from the east.

125
00:11:19,362 --> 00:11:20,487
Who are you people?

126
00:11:20,902 --> 00:11:22,198
You are here.

127
00:11:22,603 --> 00:11:25,367
They are my pals. Come on in.

128
00:11:28,772 --> 00:11:30,668
- What took you so long? - I am sorry.

129
00:11:35,313 --> 00:11:38,977
The swirling clouds surrounding the peak of the mountain.

130
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:42,747
The pointy pine tree branches.

131
00:11:42,982 --> 00:11:44,518
Is this...

132
00:11:45,693 --> 00:11:46,948
the original painting?

133
00:11:48,293 --> 00:11:50,257
You really do have an eye for art.

134
00:11:53,593 --> 00:11:58,072
I guess Wolseongdang really does buy and sell rare artwork.

135
00:11:58,073 --> 00:12:00,172
What would happen if it gets torn...

136
00:12:00,173 --> 00:12:01,398
Stop.

137
00:12:01,642 --> 00:12:05,007
Do not even touch it. It is worth four houses.

138
00:12:05,412 --> 00:12:07,337
What? Four houses?

139
00:12:10,343 --> 00:12:12,747
I am finally done.

140
00:12:13,012 --> 00:12:16,077
Hey, take a look. What do you think?

141
00:12:18,853 --> 00:12:21,357
You really are talented.

142
00:12:22,323 --> 00:12:23,922
You actually copied that.

143
00:12:23,923 --> 00:12:26,332
You made it look just like the original copy.

144
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:29,357
What are the virtues of making imitations?

145
00:12:29,463 --> 00:12:32,202
First, copy the techniques.

146
00:12:32,203 --> 00:12:35,172
Second, portray the energy in the original work.

147
00:12:35,173 --> 00:12:38,737
Third, it needs to be exactly the same.

148
00:12:39,543 --> 00:12:44,278
Will you stop being so arrogant?

149
00:12:44,713 --> 00:12:46,448
Okay, fine.

150
00:12:48,622 --> 00:12:51,222
I bet you my precious brush...

151
00:12:51,223 --> 00:12:54,422
that not even Prince Yangmyeong, the lover of arts,

152
00:12:54,423 --> 00:12:56,891
will not be able to notice that mine is an imitation.

153
00:12:56,892 --> 00:12:58,028
Really?

154
00:13:01,362 --> 00:13:04,832
My gosh, why did they have to build the storage here?

155
00:13:04,833 --> 00:13:06,731
I will never come back here again.

156
00:13:06,732 --> 00:13:09,538
Did you guys ever hear about...

157
00:13:09,543 --> 00:13:11,237
the owner of Wolseongdang?

158
00:13:11,313 --> 00:13:12,411
Ilwolseong?

159
00:13:12,412 --> 00:13:15,212
He is known to be the richest man in Guanyang.

160
00:13:15,213 --> 00:13:17,308
The most famous merchant in this country.

161
00:13:17,313 --> 00:13:19,781
That makes sense seeing that he was able to buy "Sochundo."

162
00:13:19,782 --> 00:13:21,922
That is not all.

163
00:13:21,923 --> 00:13:24,521
There are tons of original artworks in Wolseongdang.

164
00:13:24,522 --> 00:13:25,617
You are right.

165
00:13:25,693 --> 00:13:29,318
There is another big secret.

166
00:13:30,122 --> 00:13:31,661
If you write a question...

167
00:13:31,662 --> 00:13:33,891
and put it inside the box in front of Wolseongdang,

168
00:13:33,892 --> 00:13:35,631
Ilwolseong writes you back...

169
00:13:35,632 --> 00:13:39,072
saying you will have to pay a price for the answer.

170
00:13:39,073 --> 00:13:42,602
In other words, Ilwolseong is an informant...

171
00:13:42,603 --> 00:13:45,408
who knows everything.

172
00:13:46,973 --> 00:13:48,641
But you must be careful.

173
00:13:48,642 --> 00:13:53,352
Apparently, no one has ever seen his face.

174
00:13:53,353 --> 00:13:55,352
He speaks from an adjoining room,

175
00:13:55,353 --> 00:13:56,922
and you can only hear his voice...

176
00:13:56,923 --> 00:13:59,288
that does not sound like it belongs to a human.

177
00:14:00,022 --> 00:14:03,288
And they say whoever sees his face...

178
00:14:03,862 --> 00:14:05,727
will get beheaded.

179
00:14:06,293 --> 00:14:09,227
You and that darn mouth of yours.

180
00:14:09,902 --> 00:14:13,068
Do not believe him. Half of what he says is a lie.

181
00:14:13,732 --> 00:14:16,798
What? Does that mean you believe me half of the time?

182
00:14:17,343 --> 00:14:19,707
Unfortunately, I am not even interested in the other half.

183
00:14:19,872 --> 00:14:21,107
Ilwolseong?

184
00:14:21,612 --> 00:14:23,007
Hey, wait up.

185
00:14:43,732 --> 00:14:46,172
Yoo Si Hong, the younger brother of Yeon's emperor,

186
00:14:46,173 --> 00:14:48,597
is coming here as a messenger?

187
00:14:49,173 --> 00:14:50,802
That is unusual.

188
00:14:50,803 --> 00:14:52,972
Is there a special reason why...

189
00:14:52,973 --> 00:14:55,207
you chose to work at Jangwangjang today?

190
00:14:55,642 --> 00:14:57,011
According to the stars last night,

191
00:14:57,012 --> 00:14:59,477
someone special will come today from the east.

192
00:14:59,912 --> 00:15:02,918
The entrance of Jangwangjang is facing the east.

193
00:15:03,482 --> 00:15:05,048
Can you guess whom it might be?

194
00:15:10,463 --> 00:15:11,627
I am not sure.

195
00:15:12,793 --> 00:15:15,158
I wonder whom that special person will be.

196
00:15:18,933 --> 00:15:19,933
Hello.

197
00:15:19,934 --> 00:15:21,938
Jung, are you there?

198
00:15:22,372 --> 00:15:26,068
Goodness, look who is here. It is Painter Hong.

199
00:15:26,443 --> 00:15:27,911
I would like to get paid first.

200
00:15:27,912 --> 00:15:29,678
First, let me take a look at the painting.

201
00:15:31,482 --> 00:15:34,781
It is hard to tell which one is the original copy.

202
00:15:34,782 --> 00:15:36,682
This is why I like you.

203
00:15:36,683 --> 00:15:40,548
How should I put it? You have no pride as a painter.

204
00:15:41,093 --> 00:15:43,558
They both look exactly the same.

205
00:15:43,892 --> 00:15:44,932
Is that a compliment?

206
00:15:44,933 --> 00:15:46,062
It is a great compliment.

207
00:15:46,063 --> 00:15:48,261
Most painters who draw imitations...

208
00:15:48,262 --> 00:15:50,832
try very hard to leave a trace of their identity.

209
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:52,371
They are not even an aristocrat.

210
00:15:52,372 --> 00:15:55,641
Those painters also think of imitations as their work.

211
00:15:55,642 --> 00:15:57,268
I did not know that.

212
00:16:00,943 --> 00:16:02,107
Here you go.

213
00:16:03,213 --> 00:16:04,707
Let me check.

214
00:16:07,083 --> 00:16:08,178
It is the right amount.

215
00:16:14,423 --> 00:16:15,757
What is this?

216
00:16:15,992 --> 00:16:17,891
It is my gesture of gratitude.

217
00:16:17,892 --> 00:16:20,428
Gosh, why are you acting like you are going to quit?

218
00:16:20,492 --> 00:16:23,861
That is right. I have earned enough money for my father's medicine.

219
00:16:23,862 --> 00:16:29,038
Thus, that is going to be my last imitation.

220
00:16:29,973 --> 00:16:34,268
Keep quiet about all my works as you have promised.

221
00:16:37,012 --> 00:16:38,808
You are quitting?

222
00:16:38,853 --> 00:16:40,908
Well, okay.

223
00:16:41,382 --> 00:16:42,617
Painter Hong.

224
00:16:42,953 --> 00:16:47,491
Drawing imitations is very hard to quit.

225
00:16:47,492 --> 00:16:49,357
It is like a drug.

226
00:16:57,162 --> 00:16:58,967
What is with you guys?

227
00:17:00,702 --> 00:17:01,898
What is with us?

228
00:17:04,612 --> 00:17:05,938
Do you really not know?

229
00:17:06,013 --> 00:17:09,178
We favored you and treated you like a real painter,

230
00:17:10,182 --> 00:17:12,277
and that must have caused you to become arrogant.

231
00:17:13,353 --> 00:17:15,022
Let me see.

232
00:17:15,023 --> 00:17:18,088
I cannot hurt your wrist.

233
00:17:20,192 --> 00:17:22,987
Are you threatening me?

234
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:28,262
Have you forgotten who I am?

235
00:17:28,263 --> 00:17:31,272
Of course not. You are the only female painter in this city.

236
00:17:31,273 --> 00:17:32,997
The only female of the Baekyu Painters Society.

237
00:17:33,472 --> 00:17:37,941
What do you think this will do to the reputation of Wolseongdang...

238
00:17:37,942 --> 00:17:39,737
that is known to be the best art studio?

239
00:17:42,182 --> 00:17:45,651
What? Are you going to cut me with that?

240
00:17:45,652 --> 00:17:46,908
Go ahead.

241
00:17:47,412 --> 00:17:48,517
Wait.

242
00:17:50,222 --> 00:17:52,188
Here is my wrist.

243
00:18:05,902 --> 00:18:08,037
You are bolder than most men.

244
00:18:13,942 --> 00:18:17,441
You are wiser than most men.

245
00:18:17,442 --> 00:18:20,007
Leave before I change my mind.

246
00:18:22,882 --> 00:18:24,348
You had better not change your mind.

247
00:18:57,823 --> 00:18:59,047
What are you doing?

248
00:19:01,962 --> 00:19:05,457
Is there someone here?

249
00:19:06,862 --> 00:19:08,398
What is with you? I told you to leave.

250
00:19:10,362 --> 00:19:12,267
Do not talk nonsense and just go.

251
00:19:14,603 --> 00:19:16,037
Okay.

252
00:19:17,642 --> 00:19:20,838
I will be off now. Thank you for everything.

253
00:19:21,682 --> 00:19:22,977
Goodbye to you too.

254
00:19:25,783 --> 00:19:28,621
Are you really going to let her leave?

255
00:19:28,622 --> 00:19:31,017
Just get ready to go to the capital city.

256
00:19:31,353 --> 00:19:33,721
The lord in Bukchon-ri is waiting for us.

257
00:19:33,722 --> 00:19:35,658
Do not get it mixed with the original artwork.

258
00:19:47,702 --> 00:19:51,742
Goodness, the color is so beautiful.

259
00:19:51,743 --> 00:19:53,042
Do you see that?

260
00:19:53,043 --> 00:19:56,138
This color comes from a turtle that lived for 10,000 years.

261
00:19:56,243 --> 00:19:59,151
A turtle with a gold shell and a yellow neck.

262
00:19:59,152 --> 00:20:02,451
It is a medicine that was made with a 10,000-year-old ingredient.

263
00:20:02,452 --> 00:20:05,948
Unless it's a real 10,000-year gold turtle pill,

264
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:08,047
it can't be this color.

265
00:20:08,823 --> 00:20:10,057
Okay.

266
00:20:10,293 --> 00:20:11,628
I like it.

267
00:20:23,543 --> 00:20:26,072
If you take just one of these pills,

268
00:20:26,073 --> 00:20:28,842
from the moment you take it, its effects...

