537
00:39:01,592 --> 00:39:05,162
My gosh, she's one feisty woman.

538
00:39:05,163 --> 00:39:06,392
Stop right there, you jerk!

539
00:39:06,393 --> 00:39:07,631
Wait, move aside.

540
00:39:07,632 --> 00:39:08,957
My money!

541
00:39:10,833 --> 00:39:12,158
What's going on?

542
00:39:15,273 --> 00:39:17,897
It looks like there is a ruckus here.

543
00:39:21,842 --> 00:39:23,537
Goodness, Hoo.

544
00:39:24,112 --> 00:39:26,747
It's great to run into you in a place like this.

545
00:39:27,612 --> 00:39:28,877
Yes, Yul.

546
00:39:29,183 --> 00:39:31,982
Were you writing poems with other scholars here?

547
00:39:31,983 --> 00:39:33,118
Yes.

548
00:39:33,592 --> 00:39:36,691
Nice to meet you. My name is Mae Hyang.

549
00:39:36,692 --> 00:39:39,122
You're Mae Hyang, the flower of Simcheonggak.

550
00:39:39,123 --> 00:39:42,727
You must be Prince Joohyang. I've heard so much about you.

551
00:39:44,463 --> 00:39:47,098
You can all meet later.

552
00:39:47,233 --> 00:39:50,837
I'm glad you came. You should join us.

553
00:39:52,503 --> 00:39:55,667
I'll have to postpone it.

554
00:39:55,942 --> 00:39:57,937
I have an urgent engagement.

555
00:39:59,753 --> 00:40:03,321
You're always so serious. We never have any fun.

556
00:40:03,322 --> 00:40:05,752
How do you always remain the same?

557
00:40:05,753 --> 00:40:09,321
People say they'll die if they suddenly change.

558
00:40:09,322 --> 00:40:12,861
Goodness, this isn't the only day for us.

559
00:40:12,862 --> 00:40:16,062
You'll be holding a painting contest soon.

560
00:40:16,063 --> 00:40:17,702
The two of us can spend...

561
00:40:17,703 --> 00:40:19,397
all night drinking together.

562
00:40:19,503 --> 00:40:20,627
What?

563
00:40:21,003 --> 00:40:23,267
Will you really come, Hoo?

564
00:40:25,273 --> 00:40:28,372
It looks like this contest will go down in history.

565
00:40:28,373 --> 00:40:31,508
Then I hope you all have fun.

566
00:40:33,183 --> 00:40:35,178
Goodbye, Hoo.

567
00:40:49,802 --> 00:40:51,631
Are you Ilwolseong?

568
00:40:51,632 --> 00:40:54,067
Yes, my lord. Please take a seat.

569
00:40:54,672 --> 00:40:55,828
Sure.

570
00:41:00,172 --> 00:41:03,138
Did you read through the request?

571
00:41:06,683 --> 00:41:10,377
"There was a precious jade in green in a place beyond anyone's reach."

572
00:41:10,683 --> 00:41:14,787
"Recently, a night prowler has come and tried to steal the jade."

573
00:41:15,192 --> 00:41:18,488
"Was it just a petty thief who was blinded by the jade?"

574
00:41:18,822 --> 00:41:21,227
"Or was it a big thief who put out his life..."

575
00:41:21,433 --> 00:41:22,727
"because he knew its worth?"

576
00:41:23,203 --> 00:41:25,928
Yes. Do you understand...

577
00:41:26,233 --> 00:41:27,598
my concern?

578
00:41:30,842 --> 00:41:33,138
The green jade must be a jade marble.

579
00:41:33,313 --> 00:41:36,638
In other words, it's your brother, the Crown Prince's realm.

580
00:41:36,782 --> 00:41:38,707
The unreachable place must be the sky.

581
00:41:39,183 --> 00:41:42,408
In a nutshell, this means the Crown Prince's palace.

582
00:41:44,353 --> 00:41:45,548
And?

583
00:41:45,722 --> 00:41:47,388
If this was a petty thief,

584
00:41:47,722 --> 00:41:50,817
you wouldn't have stepped up yourself.

585
00:41:51,463 --> 00:41:53,227
I'm sure it's a big thief.

586
00:41:54,092 --> 00:41:56,698
Such a thief believes he's a big, nobleman.

587
00:41:57,532 --> 00:41:58,897
And a man like that...

588
00:41:59,433 --> 00:42:02,167
reached out to the unreachable sky,

589
00:42:03,942 --> 00:42:05,798
it can only mean treason.

590
00:42:07,043 --> 00:42:10,638
What's your ground for that conclusion?

591
00:42:20,422 --> 00:42:22,017
I heard the Crown Prince...

592
00:42:22,592 --> 00:42:26,627
came across an assassin during his trip to the hot spring.

593
00:42:26,963 --> 00:42:30,058
Was this found on the paper?

594
00:42:30,862 --> 00:42:33,167
If that's not a sign of treason,

595
00:42:34,333 --> 00:42:35,732
what else could it mean?

596
00:42:35,733 --> 00:42:36,997
Are you saying...

597
00:42:37,773 --> 00:42:41,808
the incident of that assassin was an act of treason?

598
00:42:42,543 --> 00:42:43,707
Do you...

599
00:42:44,282 --> 00:42:45,282
truly wish to know?

600
00:42:45,283 --> 00:42:46,452
Speak!

601
00:42:46,453 --> 00:42:47,678
In that case,

602
00:42:47,713 --> 00:42:50,078
you shouldn't be here talking to me.

603
00:42:51,253 --> 00:42:53,118
You should look into a mirror.

604
00:42:54,652 --> 00:42:56,417
Wasn't it you, Prince Joohyang,

605
00:42:58,393 --> 00:43:00,727
who sent that assassin his way?

606
00:43:13,373 --> 00:43:14,808
Do you really wish...

607
00:43:15,472 --> 00:43:17,642
to die in my hands?

608
00:43:17,643 --> 00:43:18,738
If...

609
00:43:18,913 --> 00:43:21,578
the power behind this incident comes out to the light,

610
00:43:22,853 --> 00:43:26,048
then you, Prince Joohyang, who tested me with this paper,

611
00:43:28,922 --> 00:43:30,917
wouldn't be able to survive.

612
00:43:47,342 --> 00:43:48,567
You.

613
00:43:52,742 --> 00:43:53,781
No.

614
00:43:53,782 --> 00:43:55,348
Have you forgotten?

615
00:43:56,652 --> 00:43:59,048
You promised not to pry into...

616
00:44:00,322 --> 00:44:01,848
my identity.

617
00:44:05,922 --> 00:44:08,258
What persuaded Zhuge Liang...

618
00:44:09,132 --> 00:44:10,798
wasn't a sword.

619
00:44:12,603 --> 00:44:15,897
I do not believe you're an impatient man,

620
00:44:16,603 --> 00:44:18,567
because you still...

621
00:44:18,742 --> 00:44:21,468
let the current king live in peace and safety.

622
00:44:25,483 --> 00:44:26,747
You will...

623
00:44:29,453 --> 00:44:31,848
meet me again in good time.

624
00:44:41,032 --> 00:44:43,428
This was my test.

625
00:44:43,703 --> 00:44:45,558
Your wisdom and boldness are...

626
00:44:45,603 --> 00:44:47,468
as great as I've heard, Ilwolseong.

627
00:44:47,672 --> 00:44:49,937
I look forward to the day we meet again.

628
00:44:58,183 --> 00:44:59,477
Should I track him?

629
00:44:59,953 --> 00:45:01,107
No.

630
00:45:01,983 --> 00:45:04,348
He's not a man who'll kneel before my sword.

631
00:45:06,353 --> 00:45:08,118
- Let's go. - Yes, Your Highness.

632
00:45:24,273 --> 00:45:26,808
You! You fraud!

633
00:45:28,172 --> 00:45:30,877
Give me my money. Give me my money back!

634
00:45:31,012 --> 00:45:32,881
I don't know anything!

635
00:45:32,882 --> 00:45:34,511
I just did as Jung asked!

636
00:45:34,512 --> 00:45:36,417
What? Jung?

637
00:45:36,422 --> 00:45:38,017
Is Wolseongdang a part of this too?

638
00:45:38,183 --> 00:45:40,287
It was an organized crime, wasn't it?

639
00:45:42,192 --> 00:45:43,192
I don't know anything.

640
00:45:43,193 --> 00:45:46,287
Stop right there, you scammer of Wolseongdang!

641
00:45:47,563 --> 00:45:50,901
Did I just hear that right?

642
00:45:50,902 --> 00:45:54,567
Yes, she clearly said, "You scammer..."

643
00:45:55,003 --> 00:45:57,497
"of Wolseongdang!"

644
00:46:00,643 --> 00:46:03,241
Tell Moo Young to find out everything that happened...

645
00:46:03,242 --> 00:46:04,607
in Wolseongdang to this day.

646
00:46:05,242 --> 00:46:06,477
Yes, my lord.

647
00:46:07,112 --> 00:46:08,712
Let's go, that's it.

648
00:46:08,713 --> 00:46:10,952
Yes, did I keep you waiting?

649
00:46:10,953 --> 00:46:12,821
Don't mention it, Your Highness.

650
00:46:12,822 --> 00:46:14,421
It's not like the sun has come up.

651
00:46:14,422 --> 00:46:15,491
What did you say?

652
00:46:15,492 --> 00:46:18,258
Are you saying I become wasted every single day?

653
00:46:19,262 --> 00:46:20,558
Anyway,

654
00:46:20,992 --> 00:46:23,497
don't you think you stop by the gisaeng house too often?

655
00:46:23,603 --> 00:46:26,627
What can I do? I get conscious of what people think of me.

656
00:46:26,703 --> 00:46:27,868
You do?

657
00:46:28,003 --> 00:46:30,471
They say my power has grown tremendously big.

658
00:46:30,472 --> 00:46:31,997
What power, Your Highness?

659
00:46:32,543 --> 00:46:36,542
The problem is that I only associate with the nobleman.

660
00:46:36,543 --> 00:46:39,682
I mean, it's not easy for a prince of a nation...

661
00:46:39,683 --> 00:46:42,812
to look this handsome and to have excellent calligraphy.

662
00:46:42,813 --> 00:46:45,182
If this handsome prince must live with a misunderstanding...

663
00:46:45,183 --> 00:46:47,721
because of my love for literature and arts,

664
00:46:47,722 --> 00:46:50,187
then I do not mind living my life like this.

665
00:46:50,523 --> 00:46:52,522
I shouldn't have said that.

666
00:46:52,523 --> 00:46:55,031
No, you can say that once again.

667
00:46:55,032 --> 00:46:57,462
And start over at my handsome looks.

668
00:46:57,463 --> 00:47:00,167
The handsome prince...

669
00:47:07,442 --> 00:47:09,767
This is why I like you.

670
00:47:11,282 --> 00:47:12,607
Jung...

671
00:47:14,983 --> 00:47:16,348
Wolseongdang.

672
00:47:24,922 --> 00:47:26,991
Hey, what is this?

673
00:47:26,992 --> 00:47:29,457
Anyway, what's with your face?

674
00:47:31,302 --> 00:47:33,727
I need your help. Gather round.

675
00:47:35,003 --> 00:47:36,368
What happened is...

676
00:47:40,313 --> 00:47:43,908
Now, this is a painting of a bamboo by Wun Dong of Qing.

677
00:47:44,012 --> 00:47:46,452
I hear this place has the biggest collection...

678
00:47:46,453 --> 00:47:48,412
and that you sell the paintings...

679
00:47:48,413 --> 00:47:51,482
at a handsome price, so I decided to come by.

680
00:47:51,483 --> 00:47:52,817
You're at the right place.

681
00:47:56,463 --> 00:47:59,861
That costs over 100 Yang of silver.

682
00:47:59,862 --> 00:48:02,328
Be careful. Be very careful with it.

683
00:48:04,262 --> 00:48:06,062
I'll contact you once the painting is sold.

684
00:48:06,063 --> 00:48:07,702
You can relax and wait.

685
00:48:07,703 --> 00:48:10,267
Roll it up. Careful.

686
00:48:10,342 --> 00:48:12,738
To the left. That's it.

687
00:48:13,842 --> 00:48:15,037
Is anybody here?

688
00:48:18,842 --> 00:48:19,881
What is it?

689
00:48:19,882 --> 00:48:21,781
We heard you copy the paintings people leave here...

690
00:48:21,782 --> 00:48:24,122
and sell them back as if it's the genuine piece.

691
00:48:24,123 --> 00:48:26,477
Search through.

692
00:48:26,523 --> 00:48:27,687
- Yes. - Yes.

693
00:48:28,123 --> 00:48:30,861
Search for what? What are you doing?

694
00:48:30,862 --> 00:48:33,727
What is this? Who's trying to frame me like this?

695
00:48:37,933 --> 00:48:40,397
This isn't an imitation. It's the real one.

696
00:48:41,402 --> 00:48:42,528
Painter Choi.

697
00:48:46,643 --> 00:48:49,567
He's a painter of junior eighth rank at Gohwawon.

698
00:48:49,842 --> 00:48:53,348
He's here to evaluate this to tell us if this is a copy.

699
00:48:56,753 --> 00:48:58,118
It was copied.

700
00:48:59,893 --> 00:49:01,551
What kind of nonsense is this?

701
00:49:01,552 --> 00:49:03,147
This isn't a copy!

702
00:49:03,492 --> 00:49:06,587
Why is there an insect in a bamboo painting by Wun Dong?

703
00:49:06,663 --> 00:49:08,558
- What? - That's impossible.

704
00:49:08,893 --> 00:49:12,497
Also, this paper came from Moonsung, right across the street.

705
00:49:14,003 --> 00:49:15,167
Look.

706
00:49:16,273 --> 00:49:18,267
There's the mark for Moonsung.

707
00:49:19,442 --> 00:49:20,638
This can't be.

708
00:49:20,942 --> 00:49:22,167
This can't be right!

709
00:49:23,112 --> 00:49:24,908
- Arrest him. - Yes.

710
00:49:25,012 --> 00:49:27,308
This is unfair. I've been framed!

711
00:49:27,483 --> 00:49:29,182
I don't know anything about this.

712
00:49:29,183 --> 00:49:30,817
I'm not like that!

713
00:49:32,253 --> 00:49:33,392
It's not a big deal.

714
00:49:33,393 --> 00:49:35,548
I was just there to talk.

715
00:49:36,253 --> 00:49:37,517
It's not a big deal.

716
00:50:16,032 --> 00:50:17,932
It's not a big deal.

717
00:50:17,933 --> 00:50:21,167
- I can't believe that man. - What a shame.

718
00:50:22,333 --> 00:50:23,971
Hong Cheon Gi, you brat. It was you, wasn't it?

719
00:50:23,972 --> 00:50:25,671
Are you out of your mind?

720
00:50:25,672 --> 00:50:28,511
You'll pay for this! You're just an insect!

721
00:50:28,512 --> 00:50:30,537
I will crush you!

722
00:50:31,512 --> 00:50:34,508
That made me feel so much better.

723
00:51:02,713 --> 00:51:04,281
Is that good enough?

724
00:51:04,282 --> 00:51:07,147
You should be able to handle most thugs now.

725
00:51:09,753 --> 00:51:11,477
Did you ask about the gisaeng house incident?

726
00:51:12,183 --> 00:51:15,917
Vice-chief Jung Seon Rye had been making a profit selling copies.

727
00:51:16,422 --> 00:51:19,691
A painter who provided the copies wanted to quit,

728
00:51:19,692 --> 00:51:22,491
so he deceived her and took her money.

729
00:51:22,492 --> 00:51:24,162
And she found out.

730
00:51:24,163 --> 00:51:28,028
Yes, and because of that, Jung Seon Rye was arrested today.

731
00:51:28,532 --> 00:51:29,532
Was he?

732
00:51:29,533 --> 00:51:33,198
It seems he got caught selling forgeries.

733
00:51:33,842 --> 00:51:37,812
Do you mean he was arrested because of the copycat painter?

734
00:51:37,813 --> 00:51:39,008
Yes.

735
00:51:46,753 --> 00:51:48,651
Close Wolseongdang...

736
00:51:48,652 --> 00:51:51,457
and find the copycat painter to find out more.

737
00:51:56,532 --> 00:51:59,957
My lord, it is time to go to the Palace.

738
00:52:01,072 --> 00:52:02,872
If this was not treason,

739
00:52:02,873 --> 00:52:05,567
would anyone have attacked the Crown Prince?

740
00:52:06,373 --> 00:52:09,207
Dozens of soldiers failed to catch the assassin.

741
00:52:10,012 --> 00:52:11,781
I find that hard to believe.

742
00:52:11,782 --> 00:52:13,241
Of the Five Polar Stars within...

743
00:52:13,242 --> 00:52:14,752
the Small Purple Custer indicating the palace,

744
00:52:14,753 --> 00:52:16,881
the Crown Prince's star is bright and strong,

745
00:52:16,882 --> 00:52:20,388
so you need not worry about his safety.

746
00:52:22,322 --> 00:52:23,687
Is that so?

747
00:52:24,322 --> 00:52:29,162
What I wonder is, shouldn't we find out who's threatening us...

748
00:52:29,163 --> 00:52:31,401
and punish them for it?

749
00:52:31,402 --> 00:52:33,571
I heard that when a king causes bloodshed,

750
00:52:33,572 --> 00:52:36,198
it stays with the family for a thousand years.

751
00:52:37,302 --> 00:52:42,207
You are still concerned about the blood your late father shed.

752
00:52:42,842 --> 00:52:46,207
Times like this is when you must be even more resolute.

753
00:52:47,152 --> 00:52:48,348
Yes.

754
00:52:50,353 --> 00:52:51,778
I should.

755
00:52:53,992 --> 00:52:55,448
Come closer.

756
00:53:06,103 --> 00:53:08,131
From now on, out of the Five Polar Stars,

757
00:53:08,132 --> 00:53:11,468
keep a close eye on the second and third stars that represent...

758
00:53:12,273 --> 00:53:14,167
Joohyang and Yangmyeong.

759
00:53:14,413 --> 00:53:17,738
That is my special and secret command to you.

760
00:53:18,242 --> 00:53:20,008
I will do as commanded.

761
00:53:21,683 --> 00:53:24,747
Do you still have no memory of the past?

762
00:53:26,722 --> 00:53:27,817
I do not.

763
00:53:27,922 --> 00:53:32,118
I still remember nothing right after the rainmaking ritual 19 years ago.

764
00:53:33,463 --> 00:53:34,587
However,

765
00:53:36,592 --> 00:53:40,158
sometimes, bits and pieces of my memory return.

766
00:53:42,733 --> 00:53:46,167
It's a relief to hear you're making progress.

767
00:53:46,813 --> 00:53:47,937
Yes.

768
00:53:49,242 --> 00:53:50,837
It's a great relief.

769
00:53:59,822 --> 00:54:00,917
Your Majesty.

770
00:54:02,822 --> 00:54:05,158
I may have no memory of that day,

771
00:54:05,922 --> 00:54:08,227
but how could I forget absolutely everything?

772
00:54:09,262 --> 00:54:12,528
Until those who killed my father...

773
00:54:12,963 --> 00:54:17,368
and ruined my family and my life pay the price,

774
00:54:21,213 --> 00:54:24,078
I can never forget...

775
00:54:24,483 --> 00:54:27,348
or stop what I'm doing.

776
00:54:30,012 --> 00:54:32,147
- Are you sure? - Yes.

777
00:54:32,623 --> 00:54:33,718
Boss.

778
00:54:35,023 --> 00:54:36,522
What took you so long?

779
00:54:36,523 --> 00:54:39,417
They demanded triple the amount this time.

780
00:54:40,492 --> 00:54:43,897
They took triple the bribe and treated me like this?

781
00:54:44,103 --> 00:54:45,962
He said you should be grateful they're letting you go.

782
00:54:45,963 --> 00:54:47,227
Don't.

783
00:54:47,733 --> 00:54:49,167
Hong Cheon Gi.

784
00:54:49,773 --> 00:54:51,167
Where is she?

785
00:54:53,373 --> 00:54:55,437
Good riddance, Jung Seon Rye.

786
00:54:55,672 --> 00:54:56,868
The jerk.

787
00:55:02,183 --> 00:55:05,147
Getting revenge doesn't mean I'll get the money back.

788
00:55:05,583 --> 00:55:06,948
My gosh.

789
00:55:12,793 --> 00:55:16,901
All that happened to you were out of everyone's control.

790
00:55:16,902 --> 00:55:18,658
It wasn't your fault.

791
00:55:19,862 --> 00:55:21,428
That random comment...

792
00:55:23,302 --> 00:55:25,238
still offers some comfort.

793
00:55:27,342 --> 00:55:28,437
Yes.

794
00:55:28,672 --> 00:55:29,968
Hey, Nuisance.

795
00:55:30,483 --> 00:55:32,377
What do you want now?

796
00:55:33,183 --> 00:55:36,381
Wolseongdang Jung Seon Rye conned me out of 50 Yang.

797
00:55:36,382 --> 00:55:39,377
His master Ilwolseong must give me 100 Yang.

798
00:55:40,822 --> 00:55:41,822
My gosh.

799
00:55:41,823 --> 00:55:44,957
You've been quite busy, Painter Hong.

800
00:55:45,963 --> 00:55:47,828
What do you want from...

801
00:55:48,293 --> 00:55:49,428
me?

802
00:55:49,463 --> 00:55:50,662
What do you think?

803
00:55:50,663 --> 00:55:54,227
You sent me to rot in prison for a while, but I didn't stay long.

804
00:55:54,733 --> 00:55:55,868
Oh?

805
00:56:00,273 --> 00:56:01,468
What, 100 Yang?

806
00:56:01,742 --> 00:56:03,877
You cheeky thing.

807
00:56:06,112 --> 00:56:08,082
- Shoot. - Darn it. Get her!

808
00:56:08,083 --> 00:56:09,508
- After her! - Get her!

809
00:56:11,652 --> 00:56:14,147
- Darn. - Stop!

810
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:17,957
Oh, no.

811
00:56:21,433 --> 00:56:23,031
Boss! Boss!

812
00:56:23,032 --> 00:56:25,758
- Boss! - Get up!

813
00:56:26,833 --> 00:56:28,127
Where is she?

814
00:56:29,402 --> 00:56:30,402
Go that way!

815
00:56:30,403 --> 00:56:31,471
Okay.

816
00:56:31,472 --> 00:56:33,037
What a brat.

817
00:56:35,143 --> 00:56:37,678
Scholar Ha, we reached the gate.

818
00:56:38,043 --> 00:56:40,881
I'll show the guard our nighttime travel permit.

819
00:56:40,882 --> 00:56:42,178
Okay.

820
00:56:46,992 --> 00:56:50,817
What? Jung? Is Wolseongdang a part of this too?

821
00:56:51,123 --> 00:56:52,488
How did I get involved?

822
00:56:55,592 --> 00:56:58,928
I don't know who you are, but please ignore me for now.

823
00:56:59,603 --> 00:57:00,698
But...

824
00:57:02,433 --> 00:57:05,167
- Who are you? - Be quiet.

825
00:57:37,873 --> 00:57:39,098
You lost her?

826
00:57:39,472 --> 00:57:42,107
It's past curfew, so she can't have left the Capital.

827
00:57:42,143 --> 00:57:43,412
Find her at all cost.

828
00:57:43,413 --> 00:57:44,678
- Yes, Boss. - Yes, Boss.

829
00:57:47,782 --> 00:57:49,778
Just wait until I get you.

830
00:57:50,152 --> 00:57:53,178
I'll break your wrist so you never draw again.

831
00:57:53,222 --> 00:57:55,388
Can this woman be...

832
00:57:59,793 --> 00:58:01,087
Who are you?

833
00:58:01,192 --> 00:58:04,432
Let me ask you something. Did you see a girl run by?

834
00:58:04,433 --> 00:58:06,227
A girl?

835
00:58:06,532 --> 00:58:08,631
May I look inside the litter?

836
00:58:08,632 --> 00:58:10,028
Let's go, Man Soo.

837
00:58:10,942 --> 00:58:12,702
Yes, sir. Let's go!

838
00:58:12,703 --> 00:58:14,611
Okay. One, two.

839
00:58:14,612 --> 00:58:15,707
Wait.

840
00:58:16,143 --> 00:58:17,611
What do you want?

841
00:58:17,612 --> 00:58:20,477
I need to see the face of the person inside.

842
00:58:20,552 --> 00:58:23,281
Do you know who this is?

843
00:58:23,282 --> 00:58:24,647
What's going on?

844
00:58:25,282 --> 00:58:27,647
It's nothing, sir.

845
00:58:28,853 --> 00:58:30,892
- You should just... - Sir.

846
00:58:30,893 --> 00:58:32,421
I don't know who you are,

847
00:58:32,422 --> 00:58:34,832
but I'm looking for a servant girl who ran off.

848
00:58:34,833 --> 00:58:36,631
I'm sure she went this way.

849
00:58:36,632 --> 00:58:38,028
I looked all around...

850
00:58:40,802 --> 00:58:42,497
I'm the only one inside.

851
00:58:42,503 --> 00:58:45,997
I cannot let you go until I see for myself.

852
00:58:46,072 --> 00:58:47,207
You can't...

853
00:58:53,183 --> 00:58:54,948
Open at your own peril.

854
00:58:56,052 --> 00:58:57,348
Red eyes?

855
00:58:58,782 --> 00:59:02,917
This litter belongs to His Majesty the King.

856
00:59:03,893 --> 00:59:05,817
Do you know what that means?

857
00:59:13,762 --> 00:59:16,102
It was ignorant of me to disturb you.

858
00:59:16,103 --> 00:59:17,372
You got lucky.

859
00:59:17,373 --> 00:59:19,537
If you had opened the window,

860
00:59:20,103 --> 00:59:22,372
you would have lost your life.

861
00:59:22,373 --> 00:59:23,638
Let's go, Man Soo.

862
00:59:24,713 --> 00:59:25,937
Let's go.

863
00:59:27,782 --> 00:59:28,977
Step aside.

864
00:59:43,663 --> 00:59:46,957
Thank you. You saved me.

865
00:59:48,373 --> 00:59:50,267
Were you very startled?

866
00:59:50,942 --> 00:59:52,497
My heart almost stopped.

867
00:59:53,103 --> 00:59:56,341
My heart almost stopped too when I saw a man in a litter...

868
00:59:56,342 --> 00:59:58,308
when I expected a woman.

869
00:59:58,782 --> 01:00:03,252
I only ride litters because I cannot see.

870
01:00:03,253 --> 01:00:04,348
Pardon?

871
01:00:07,152 --> 01:00:08,787
I see.

872
01:00:13,992 --> 01:00:17,258
Why did you help me?

873
01:00:17,703 --> 01:00:20,801
What if I really were a servant girl on the run?

874
01:00:20,802 --> 01:00:23,202
You smell of ink,

875
01:00:23,203 --> 01:00:24,441
so you can't be a servant.

876
01:00:24,442 --> 01:00:27,241
A servant wouldn't have thought of jumping into someone else's litter.

877
01:00:27,242 --> 01:00:30,207
I thought you must've had a reason.

878
01:00:32,713 --> 01:00:36,107
You're right. I'm a painter.

879
01:00:36,512 --> 01:00:38,122
You're truly impressive.

880
01:00:38,123 --> 01:00:39,417
Not at all.

881
01:00:39,453 --> 01:00:43,348
I cannot see, so I observe with smells and sounds.

882
01:00:43,722 --> 01:00:45,721
Were you waiting for someone?

883
01:00:45,722 --> 01:00:47,258
It's very late.

884
01:00:48,163 --> 01:00:49,357
Actually,

885
01:00:49,893 --> 01:00:52,798
they were chasing me from the start.

886
01:00:52,902 --> 01:00:56,298
What happened that made you so desperate?

887
01:00:59,402 --> 01:01:01,937
That fool conned me.

888
01:01:02,143 --> 01:01:04,037
He's the worst.

889
01:01:04,313 --> 01:01:07,678
Have you heard of Wolseongdang on Woonjong Street?

890
01:01:08,813 --> 01:01:09,881
I'm not sure.

891
01:01:09,882 --> 01:01:13,452
It's an art studio known for selling expensive paintings,

892
01:01:13,453 --> 01:01:16,392
but the truth is, they're a rotten bunch...

893
01:01:16,393 --> 01:01:18,861
that sell copies for the real deal to make a profit.

894
01:01:18,862 --> 01:01:21,691
He conned me and took my money,

895
01:01:21,692 --> 01:01:23,988
and I got back at him for it.

896
01:01:24,463 --> 01:01:26,702
I saw him get arrested and taken away.

897
01:01:26,703 --> 01:01:28,497
He got out so soon.

898
01:01:29,302 --> 01:01:30,567
Oh, right.

899
01:01:30,703 --> 01:01:33,537
Ilwolseong. He must've gotten him out.

900
01:01:33,672 --> 01:01:35,241
I heard he was dangerous.

901
01:01:35,242 --> 01:01:37,381
- Ilwolseong? - Yes.

902
01:01:37,382 --> 01:01:40,337
He's the worst of them all, and very dangerous too.

903
01:01:40,442 --> 01:01:44,578
Anyone who knows his identity ends up getting killed off.

904
01:01:46,753 --> 01:01:48,921
I think I heard of him,

905
01:01:48,922 --> 01:01:51,462
but isn't he knowledgeable and virtuous...

906
01:01:51,463 --> 01:01:52,618
What?

907
01:01:52,623 --> 01:01:54,491
That sounds as preposterous...

908
01:01:54,492 --> 01:01:56,591
as a date getting struck by lightning on a clear day.

909
01:01:56,592 --> 01:01:59,058
That's not true at all.

910
01:02:03,103 --> 01:02:04,267
Are you...

911
01:02:05,273 --> 01:02:06,638
Ilwolseong...

912
01:02:10,472 --> 01:02:12,877
I mean, you're not his friend, are you?

913
01:02:14,253 --> 01:02:16,308
- As if I would be. - Good.

914
01:02:16,612 --> 01:02:20,118
Why would you tease me? My heart almost stopped.

915
01:02:20,793 --> 01:02:22,317
Here it is.

916
01:02:22,822 --> 01:02:25,591
That's great. Why did you tease me?

917
01:02:25,592 --> 01:02:27,528
My heart almost sank.

918
01:02:28,293 --> 01:02:31,631
Why does she remind me of her?

919
01:02:31,632 --> 01:02:33,002
The road's uneven from here.

920
01:02:33,003 --> 01:02:34,167
- Okay. - Okay.

921
01:02:45,742 --> 01:02:46,877
Your eyes...

922
01:02:47,813 --> 01:02:50,607
are really beautiful.

923
01:02:51,722 --> 01:02:54,448
They're like red jewels.

924
01:03:02,762 --> 01:03:03,957
Are you okay?

925
01:03:04,463 --> 01:03:06,598
Yes, I'm fine.

926
01:03:09,833 --> 01:03:12,098
No one has said that to me before.

927
01:03:12,472 --> 01:03:14,468
People see my eyes...

928
01:03:14,913 --> 01:03:16,607
and call me a freak.

929
01:03:16,742 --> 01:03:17,781
What?

930
01:03:17,782 --> 01:03:20,238
About such beautiful eyes?

931
01:03:20,282 --> 01:03:23,381
They're the prettiest eyes I've ever seen.

932
01:03:23,382 --> 01:03:24,618
I mean it.

933
01:03:24,722 --> 01:03:26,718
- Oh, dear. - Gosh.

934
01:03:50,273 --> 01:03:53,107
Are you all right? It's so rocky.

935
01:04:00,753 --> 01:04:01,948
Sir?

936
01:04:03,393 --> 01:04:05,022
What's wrong?

937
01:04:05,023 --> 01:04:07,017
Do you feel unwell?

938
01:04:18,572 --> 01:04:20,202
I need you to get out.

939
01:04:20,203 --> 01:04:21,337
Pardon?

940
01:04:21,643 --> 01:04:22,941
Just like that?

941
01:04:22,942 --> 01:04:25,381
Man Soo, stop the litter.

942
01:04:25,382 --> 01:04:26,607
Pardon?

943
01:04:26,942 --> 01:04:29,281
Yes, sir. Put down the litter.

944
01:04:29,282 --> 01:04:30,448
Sir.

945
01:04:41,933 --> 01:04:45,058
Sir, can you tell me your name?

946
01:04:47,003 --> 01:04:50,497
- Let's go now, Man Soo. - Yes, Sir Scholar.

947
01:04:52,143 --> 01:04:53,298
"Scholar"?

948
01:04:54,342 --> 01:04:55,767
Get back safely.

949
01:04:58,083 --> 01:04:59,083
Let's go.

950
01:04:59,084 --> 01:05:00,977
One, two, three.

951
01:05:01,782 --> 01:05:04,517
Wait, sir! Can I know your name?

952
01:05:05,353 --> 01:05:06,578
Sir...

953
01:05:16,333 --> 01:05:19,857
She'll be okay on her own at night, won't she?

954
01:05:20,663 --> 01:05:22,667
The Capital's very close, but still.

955
01:05:23,433 --> 01:05:24,567
What?

956
01:05:32,942 --> 01:05:36,377
How could he tell me to get out just like that?

957
01:05:41,793 --> 01:05:44,287
I wonder what happened to Nuisance and Frown.

958
01:05:54,672 --> 01:05:56,131
Why is he moving so much?

959
01:05:56,132 --> 01:05:59,341
Will you hold on tight? The road's rough as it is.

960
01:05:59,342 --> 01:06:00,968
The litter's shaking.

961
01:06:04,213 --> 01:06:06,778
This is a bit serious.

962
01:06:06,983 --> 01:06:08,348
Stand still.

963
01:06:11,052 --> 01:06:13,122
Put down the litter.

964
01:06:13,123 --> 01:06:14,517
Do it, now!

965
01:06:47,483 --> 01:06:50,218
Sir, you're okay, aren't you?

966
01:07:13,282 --> 01:07:14,678
Sir.

967
01:07:53,083 --> 01:07:54,618
What is that?

968
01:07:58,922 --> 01:08:00,591
It's a ghost.

969
01:08:00,592 --> 01:08:03,388
No, it's a freak! The freak!

970
01:08:07,532 --> 01:08:08,768
Sir.

971
01:08:11,142 --> 01:08:12,398
He's gone?

972
01:08:30,123 --> 01:08:31,287
Run!

973
01:08:31,963 --> 01:08:34,058
Go. Get out of here!

974
01:08:41,203 --> 01:08:43,027
You made a mistake, Ha Ram.

975
01:08:43,633 --> 01:08:46,237
On the Winter Solstice when Yin prevails,

976
01:08:46,543 --> 01:08:48,508
you crossed the boundary.

977
01:09:09,333 --> 01:09:12,157
I found my eyes.

978
01:09:46,445 --> 01:09:48,614
(Lovers of the Red Sky)

979
01:09:48,615 --> 01:09:51,183
Something happened on Mount Inwang.

980
01:09:51,184 --> 01:09:53,583
He fell from the sky...

981
01:09:53,584 --> 01:09:55,053
and passed out.

982
01:09:55,054 --> 01:09:56,954
What do you mean the soldiers died overnight?

983
01:09:56,955 --> 01:09:59,154
The bodies are all listless.

984
01:09:59,155 --> 01:10:00,484
It's very strange.

985
01:10:00,485 --> 01:10:02,223
It's a mark of the Demon.

986
01:10:02,224 --> 01:10:04,293
Is this truly a copy?

987
01:10:04,294 --> 01:10:06,623
Find the cheeky copycat painter for me.

988
01:10:06,624 --> 01:10:09,330
- Lock her up this instant! - No!

989
01:10:09,764 --> 01:10:11,904
What's the delay when it's Hong Cheon Gi?

990
01:10:11,905 --> 01:10:14,204
Her mad father is always outside.

991
01:10:14,205 --> 01:10:15,673
Get her right now!

992
01:10:15,674 --> 01:10:18,803
Memories of the girl from the peach orchard...

993
01:10:18,804 --> 01:10:20,343
keep overlapping with her.

994
01:10:20,344 --> 01:10:21,569
Who are you?
